        <h2>To Begin: E-assessment Dummy Run</H2>
        
    <p class="c11 c15">
      <span class="c0">To avoid the hitches and glitches that might technology introduce and reduce unnecessary delays mid course, introduce a  “dummy run” early on in the semester. A dummy run should combine the assessment instruments and the assessment instructions. </span>
      
    </p>
    <p class="c11 c15">
      <span>Dummy runs offer </span>
      <span class="c27">students</span>
      <span class="c0"> three opportunities </span>
    </p>
    <ul class="c14 lst-kix_list_11-0 start">
      <li class="c32 c6">
        <span class="c0">To understand the assessment procedure </span>
      </li>
      <li class="c32 c6">
        <span class="c0">To discover if and how they might access technical support. </span>
      </li>
      <li class="c11 c6">
        <span class="c0">To provide feedback about their experience to the lecturer.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="c11 c15">
      <span>Dummy runs offer the </span>
      <span class="c27">lecturer</span>
      <span class="c0"> three opportunities</span>
    </p>
    <ul class="c14 lst-kix_list_12-0 start">
      <li class="c32 c6">
        <span class="c0">To test the link between the markbook and the assessment</span>
      </li>
      <li class="c32 c6">
        <span class="c0">To see if they can accommodate particular student’s special needs</span>
      </li>
      <li class="c11 c6">
        <span class="c0">To rectify  problems with sufficient time available in advance </span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="c11 c15">
      <span class="c0">Dummy runs should be done in the initial orientation phase of the course. From past experience, It is recommended that </span>
    </p>
    <ul class="c14 lst-kix_list_27-0 start">
      <li class="c6 c48">
        <span class="c0">A web link to the tool to technical support should be included in the notification, so that students can access instructions on how to use the tools.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="c48 c6">
        <span class="c0">Any work that is submitted (assignments, quiz, report etc) should be submitted from a computer / laptop (and not a mobile phone).</span>
      </li>
      <li class="c125 c6">
        <span class="c0">If videos are included in an assignment, the video must be uploaded to YouTube as Unlisted video, and then students should submit the URL of the video .</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="c11 c15">
      <span class="c0">The following actions that can assist students to complete assessments (whether on a dummy run or for real) should be re-enforced</span>
    </p>
    <ul class="c14 lst-kix_list_27-0">
      <li class="c48 c6">
        <span class="c0">Read the instructions – You will be clear about the the steps to follow when completing the assessment</span>
      </li>
      <li class="c48 c6">
        <span class="c0">Update your diary – You will consult the schedule and know when the assessment is, well ahead of time </span>
      </li>
      <li class="c48 c6">
        <span class="c0">Read the manual – You will be familiar with the assessment tools prior to the assessments </span>
      </li>
      <li class="c48 c6">
        <span class="c0">Be connected – You will have access to stable internet and access to data or free Wi-Fi as a back up </span>
      </li>
      <li class="c125 c6">
        <span class="c0">Be pro-active – You will avoid the last minute rush and submit assessments in due time and not at the last moment.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

        
        

        
        
        
        
